<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861216-0128 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report</HL><DD> 12/16/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UTXAEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><TEXT>   MESSERSCHMITT-BOELKOW-BLOHM G.M.B.H. said it agreed in principle with UNITED TECHNOLOGIES CORP. of the U.S. to form a joint venture to develop laser applications for industrial automation systems. Messerschmitt, a West German aerospace and technology concern, said United Technologies would contribute its patents, production process and application systems for its industrial laser technology. Messerschmitt said it would contribute its planning and production technology for flexible assembly systems. A final agreement isn't expected to be signed until early next year, the German company said. </TEXT></DOC>